A song that was released in 1963 was later directly adopted by other major bands of the 1977 punk movement. This shows it carried an intrinsic energy and simplicity that spoke to a sound that hadn't even been fully invented yet. The Trashmen themselves were a surf rock band and may not have considered themselves punk, the energy, simplicity, and raw attitude of Surfin' Bird made it a true Proto-Punk blueprint that was certainly ahead of its time.

